Art Week Miami 2023 w/ @gotthemojo

Just some key moments from an incredible Art Week/ Art Basel for 2023. 

I wanted to let everyone know how proud I am of this man @gotthemojo . It was truly an inspiration to watch him paint this wondrous mural “Liberty City” and him be recognized for his contributions to the Miami art world and the surrounding communities of Miami. It was admirable to witness how many people love Mojo and it was such a confirmation to me the validity of the loving heart he shares with me. It’s no wonder why I am so in love with him and his big beautiful soul. Not only that but to see the amount of hard work and dedication he put in, but most of all the intention in his work was and is such an honor to watch because it has even left me inspired and motivated for what’s to come for myself! 

& because you’re going to see this, Congratulations on such an abundant and blessed year for 2023, I know you’re already working for 2024 🙄 but ENJOY what’s left 🤪😘😘😘😘 Love you 🥰 (I’m gonna end it here because you think I’m ignoring you rn and you’re giving me hellllaaaaa shit 😂😂😂😂)

Home for the holidays and I’ve been living so much in the moment with my beautiful son, family, and friends that I failed on capturing any photos! I had the privilege of attending church yesterday and was reminded of the true meaning of CHRIST-mas and was surrounded by love, peace, and joy! Merry Christmas and God bless !!

Thank you God! 
2023 has been one heck of a ride! It started off challenging. I was depressed, unhappy and depending on the wrong things to fulfill me. I quit my job, I moved out of my apartment and shed myself from the material attachments I had and left everything in God’s hands. I had no idea where He was taking me but I knew I had to have faith. Flash forward to today I am in the healthiest most loving relationship living in my frequent vacay destination Miami lol, about to embark on an amazing journey this New Year. My son is abundant and in great health and that’s all I could really ask for. Life isn’t perfect but when you have the God I do life being perfect doesn’t matter. I couldn’t be any more grateful for all the beautiful moments that were shared in 2023 🫶🏽

God is love.
Cay’s Mom.
